body:
### Description

When launching the app in UWP and trying to draw on canvas with the mouse, the `Id` of the `SKTouchEventArgs` is 1 all the time. Souldn't it change?  Because now i keep continuing the same path, what I want are some new paths every time when I start drawing by pressing the mouse and moving. Should I make a workaround, because on other devices it works as expected. Only in iOS the id is somehow generated, but android and UWP they have constant values like 0 or 1, or more based on the number of fingers.

<!-- a general description goes here -->

### Code

``` csharp
private void _canvas_Touch(object sender, SKTouchEventArgs e)
{
    switch (e.ActionType)
    {
        case SKTouchAction.Entered:
            break;
        case SKTouchAction.Pressed:
            if(!_inprogressPaths.ContainsKey(e.Id))
            {
                Debug.WriteLine($"Path with Id: {e.Id} added");
                SKPath newPath = new SKPath();
                newPath.MoveTo(e.Location);
                _inprogressPaths.Add(e.Id, newPath);
            }
            break;
        case SKTouchAction.Moved:
            if(_inprogressPaths.ContainsKey(e.Id))
            {
                Debug.WriteLine($"Path with Id: {e.Id} moving...");
                switch (e.DeviceType)
                {
                    case SKTouchDeviceType.Touch:
                    case SKTouchDeviceType.Mouse when e.MouseButton == SKMouseButton.Left:
                    case SKTouchDeviceType.Pen:
                        var path = _inprogressPaths[e.Id];
                        path.LineTo(e.Location);
                        _canvas.InvalidateSurface();
                        break;
                    default:
                        break;
                }
            }
            break;
        case SKTouchAction.Released:
            if(_inprogressPaths.ContainsKey(e.Id))
            {
                _canvas.InvalidateSurface();
            }
            break;
        case SKTouchAction.Cancelled:
            break;
        case SKTouchAction.Exited:
            break;
        default:
            break;
    }

    e.Handled = true;
} 
```

### Expected Behavior

The Id of the `SKTouchEventArgs` to change every time i press the mouse button and start drawing.
<!-- a general description of what was the expected behavior or result -->

### Actual Behavior

The Id of the touch is 1 all the time
<!-- a general description of what really happened -->

### Basic Information

- Version with issue:  1.60.1
- Last known good version:  none
- IDE: Visual Studio
- Platform Target Frameworks: <!-- all that apply, remove the platforms that aren't broken or haven't had any testing -->
  - UWP:  Build 17134, version 1803
